properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 21 at 3:34AM EST until January 22 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Gaylord MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Highest gusts up to 35 kt and highest waves around 11
feet expected.

* WHERE...Seul Choix Point to 5NM West of Mackinac Bridge,
Norwood MI to 5NM West of Mackinac Bridge including Little
Traverse Bay, Sleeping Bear Point to Grand Traverse Light MI,
Point Betsie to Sleeping Bear Point MI and Manistee to Point
Betsie MI.

* WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to 4 PM EST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous highest waves
which could capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 PM EST WEDNESDAY
